message.mishanguc.absolute.description: In absolute mode, rearranging texts will ignore this line.
message.mishanguc.accept_custom_value: Type in the text field to set the value of %s.
message.mishanguc.add_first_text: Click here to add first text!
message.mishanguc.add_text.description: Add a line of text after the current selected text. The position of other texts will not be affected unless you click 'Adjust positions'.
message.mishanguc.apply_double_line_temp: Quickly add two lines arranged with one large and one smaller. This is often used in bilingual notices.
message.mishanguc.apply_left_arrow_templ: Quickly add two lines and a left-arrow. This is often used in bilingual direction instructions.
message.mishanguc.apply_right_arrow_temp: Quickly add two lines and a right-arrow. This is often used in bilingual direction instructions.
message.mishanguc.clear.confirm.descript: Click again to clear all text. Cannot be undone!
message.mishanguc.clear.description: Clear all texts. Cannot be undone!
message.mishanguc.copy_from_back.descrip: Copy the text from the back side of the sign. The horizontal align and offset will be flipped, and the arrow signs in the texts (if any) will also be horizontally flipped, in order to conform the back side. If the back side does not have text, no changes will be made.
message.mishanguc.custom_value.tooltip: Type in this text field to set the %s of the text.
message.mishanguc.flip.description: Flip the offset and alignment of the current text in the left-right direction. Hold 'Ctrl' to flip all texts.
message.mishanguc.hide_gui.note: Please note: You are currently editing the sign and the GUI is hidden. Press the "Show" button to make it visible, or press "Esc" to finish editing.
message.mishanguc.hide_gui.tooltip: Hide all screen elements so as to preview clearly.
message.mishanguc.moveDown.description: Move the current text field down. Does not affect their displaying unless you click 'Adjust positions'.
message.mishanguc.moveUp.description: Move the current text field up. Does not affect their displaying unless you click `Adjust positions`.

message.mishanguc.rearrange.tooltip: Adjust the horizontal offsets of texts. Text lines in absolute mode will be ignored.
message.mishanguc.remove_text.descriptio: Remove the current line of text.
message.mishanguc.select_button_to_set_c: Click a button and then you can type the value for it.
message.mishanguc.set_custom_value.descr: Click this button, and then click another button, and you can type the value for that.
When using keyboard to operate, focus on a button and then press the shortcut to directly edit the value for the focused button.
message.mishanguc.shade.description: May cause rendering error. Not recommended to turn on.
message.mishanguc.sign.glow_off: The sign has been removed glow

message.mishanguc.sign.wax_on: The sign has been waxed and will be not editable

modmenu.descriptionTranslation.mishanguc: The mod provides an amount of blocks and items that make a beautiful city, which includes roads, signs, lights, handrails, colored blocks and some useful tools. Thank you for using this mod. I'm looking forward to your suggestions.
narration.mishanguc.button.boolean_usage: Press this button or scroll the mouse wheel to switch value.
narration.mishanguc.button.float_usage: Press the button or scroll the mouse wheel to change value. If you want to change value via keyboard arrow keys, please press Enter or Space to activate the button. When using mouse buttons or mouse wheel to change value, you may press while holding Shift, or press with right-side mouse button to change in an inverted direction. Hold Ctrl to switch more quickly. Hold Alt to switch more precisely. Press with middle mouse button to restore to default value.
narration.mishanguc.button.float_usage.f: Use keyboard arrow keys to change value. Press Enter or Space to finish the change. Hold Ctrl to switch more quickly. Hold Alt to switch more precisely. Press both left arrow key and right arrow key to restore to default value.
narration.mishanguc.button.null: Please add and select a row of text before using this button.
